//Osteochondrosis dissecans (OCD)


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 07 - Femoropatellar joint of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled
When I select 'Osteochondrosis dissecans (OCD)' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled

And a localizer image is enabled
And 'Medial facet' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lateral facet' checkbox is enabled

And 'Cartilage intact, stable lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Chondral lesion, unstable lesion' radio button is enabled

And 'Open (juvenile form)' radio button is enabled
And 'Closed (adult form)' radio button is enabled

And 'Lesion diameter in mm' checkbox is enabled
And 'Old lesion, entirely filled with fluid' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Cartilage intact, stable lesion' radio button
Then 'Bone marrow edema' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Chondral lesion, unstable lesion' radio button
Then 'In situ' radio button is enabled
And 'Displaced' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Lesion diameter in mm' checkbox
Then 'Max. diameter in mm' input field is enabled
